summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 19021 entitled: "An ordinance relating to and providing for the improvement of 20th Avenue Northwest, from Ballard Avenue to Shilshole Avenue, all in the City of Seattle, by constructing wood walks thereon, all in accordance with Resolution No. 1456 of the city council of the City of Seattle; and providing payment therefor by the mode of "Payment in Bonds", as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle" approved August 17, 1908.
